fields.description: Responsible for managing supplier relationships across North America and South Asia. Key duties include conducting supplier outreach in the USA and Canada, researching and evaluating potential suppliers in South Asia, and performing on-site factory visits in Hamilton and Toronto to finalize supplier partnerships. Ensured smooth communication, thorough due diligence, and successful onboarding of reliable suppliers.

Conducted market research to identify and evaluate suppliers for required components across the China and India regions. Analyzed pricing, quality standards, and supplier capabilities to support efficient and cost-effective sourcing decisions.

During my time at Carmel Junior College, I excelled both academically and in extracurricular activities. As a national athlete, I represented the college with pride and dedication, showcasing my athletic prowess on a national level. Additionally, as the squad leader of Team Uranus, I effectively led my peers, fostering teamwork and achieving collective goals.

Beyond sports, I held significant leadership roles, serving as the treasurer of the Legal Literacy Club, where I managed finances and supported initiatives to promote legal awareness among students. Simultaneously, as the vice president of the Electoral Literacy Club, I organized educational sessions and engaged peers in discussions to enhance understanding of electoral processes and civic responsibilities.

These experiences at Carmel Junior College not only shaped my leadership, organizational, and teamwork skills but also instilled in me a deep commitment to academic excellence and community involvement.

fields.description:
I’m a sophomore at SRM Institute of Science and Technology (SRMIST) with a strong interest in software development and machine learning. I enjoy building practical projects that combine coding with real-world problem solving, especially in areas like web development, data analysis, and AI-based applications.

I primarily work with Python, Django, SQL, and machine learning algorithms, and I like turning ideas into functional products rather than just writing code for assignments. I’m constantly learning, experimenting, and improving my skills by building projects and exploring new technologies.

Beyond academics, I’m focused on developing a strong foundation in problem-solving, system design, and clean coding practices, with the goal of becoming a skilled and impactful software engineer.
